<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The OS_DEBUG macro is defined as empty (#define OS_DEBUG(__VA_ARGS__)). The source line OS_DEBUG("recvfrom: %s\n", strerror(errno)); therefore expands to a null statement (no-op) in the compiled code. This executed no-op can be removed without changing program behaviour, so it constitutes dead code and violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
